# Cursor Customization Rules for CBD Side Business Project

## Core Identity Reference
- **Always reference:** `@identity.md` for user background, values, and business context
- **User Profile:** 27歳、データコンサルタント、趣味（ポーカー・マラソン・お酒）
- **Core Values:** 人を笑わせる、意外性を提供する、仕事を楽しむ
- **Work Style:** 平日<1hr、休日~3hrs、自動化・効率化を最優先

## Project Context
- **Primary Goal (2024):** 固定費（約10万円）の完全回収
- **Target:** CBDサイト（https://cbd-no-hito.com/）のCVR 10%を目指す
- **Tech Stack:** WordPress/SWELL, Python, SQL, GAS, GitHub

## Critical Workflow Rules

### 1. Approval-First Principle
- **NEVER** create files, modify code, or deploy without explicit user approval
- Always present proposals with:
  - Clear rationale (数値的根拠または図解イメージ)
  - Comparison of alternatives (if applicable)
  - Expected impact/outcome
- Wait for user's "進めてよい" confirmation before execution

### 2. Data-Driven Approach
- Provide numerical justifications or visual comparisons when proposing solutions
- Reference conversion rates, time estimates, scalability metrics
- Use graphs, tables, or diagrams to illustrate options

### 3. Automation & Scalability Priority
- Prioritize "仕組み化" over one-off solutions
- Leverage GitHub, APIs, MCP integrations for repeatable workflows
- Design for minimal manual intervention

### 4. Integration & Tool Coordination
Tools to consider for ecosystem:
- **WordPress/SWELL:** Main revenue platform
- **GitHub:** Code management (themes, scripts, automation)
- **Google Drive (MCP):** Spreadsheet-based database for content/diagnosis logic
- **X (Twitter):** Auto-posting with humor/意外性
- **TikTok/Instagram:** Content automation (scripts, scheduling)
- **LINE Official:** High-CVR personal recommendations

### 5. Content & Code Style
- Inject humor and unexpected elements (ポーカー、マラソン、お酒の要素)
- Maintain professional quality while being entertaining
- Write code that is self-documenting and maintainable
- Follow WordPress/SWELL best practices

## Code & File Organization
- Use GitHub for all code (SWELL child themes, Python scripts, automation tools)
- Keep files organized by purpose (diagnosis-tools/, automation/, content-generation/)
- Document all automation workflows in WORKFLOW.md

## Communication Style
- **Language:** Always respond in Japanese
- **Tone:** Professional but friendly, data-driven, focused on solutions
- **Format:** Use visual aids (tables, code blocks, diagrams) when helpful
